Column Name	Data Type (MySQL)	Description	Example	Nullable	Business Use		
CustomerKey	INT	Unique identifier for each customer. Used to join with the Sales table.	11000	No	Identify each customer and link to sales		
Prefix	VARCHAR(10)	"Customer's title (Mr., Mrs., Ms., Dr., etc.)"	Mr.	Yes	Customer demographics		
FirstName	VARCHAR(50)	Customer's first name	John	No	Customer identification		
LastName	VARCHAR(50)	Customer's last name	Smith	No	Customer identification		
BirthDate	DATE	Customer's date of birth	7/20/1985	Yes	Calculate customer age and age groups		
MaritalStatus	CHAR(1)	"Marital status (M = Married, S = Single)"	M	Yes	Customer segmentation		
Gender	CHAR(1)	"Customer gender (M = Male, F = Female)"	F	Yes	Gender-based analysis		
EmailAddress	VARCHAR(100)	Customer's email address	john@gmail.com	Yes	Customer communication (not used in reporting)		
AnnualIncome	"DECIMAL(10,2)"	Customer's annual income	75000	Yes	Income-based customer segmentation		
TotalChildren	INT	Number of children	2	Yes	Family demographic analysis		
EducationLevel	VARCHAR(50)	Highest education level	Bachelors	Yes	Education-based customer insights		
Occupation	VARCHAR(50)	Customer occupation	Professional	Yes	Occupation-based sales analysis		
HomeOwner	VARCHAR(10)	Indicates if the customer owns a home (Yes/No)	Yes	Yes	Lifestyle segmentation		
							
							
							
							
							
							
							
							
